&lt;h2 id="bonehill">Bonehill
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/widecombe/31.jpg"
width="1600"
height="900"
srcset="https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/widecombe/31_hu_f4b814607e50117d.jpg 480w, https://dartmoorwalking.org/p/widecombe/31_hu_47fd0d5728f921a0.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Bonehill Gate where we rejoin the metalled road"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Bonehill Gate, beside Bonehill Rocks where the road descends steeply to the medieval hamlet of Bonehill (or Bunhill), constructed between 1066 and 1682.&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.heritagegateway.org.uk/Gateway/Results_Single.aspx?uid=MDV29743&amp;amp;resourceID=104" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
